  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contribution of the UNESCO Associated Schools Network (ASPnet) to Target 4.7 of the 2030 Education agenda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The UNESCO Associated Schools Network (ASPnet) links over 11,500 educational institutions in 182 countries around a common goal: to construct the defences of peace in the minds of children and young people. ASPnet focuses on 3 Thematic Action Areas: a) Global citizenship and a culture of peace and non-violence b) Sustainable development and sustainable lifestyles c) Inter-cultural learning and the appreciation of cultural diversity and heritage. The network makes an important contribution to reaching targets 4.7 and 4.a of SDG4. Members conduct pilot projects, experiment innovative approaches and test educational materials to improve the quality of education, learning and content. The ASPnet needs good governance and quality assurance in order to play its role effectively.</narrative>
  </description>
